Privacy Policy
Our product, Blood Pressure APP-pulse track ("the App"), is designed to help you track your blood pressure and health. We are committed to protecting your privacy and personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose information about you when you use the App.
What information do we collect?
When you use the App, we may collect the following types of information:
Personal information:
We may collect your name, email address, and other contact information when you create an account with us.
Health information:
We may collect information about your blood pressure and other health metrics when you use the App to monitor your health.
Healthkit
You can connect to HealthKit for data synchronization within the APP, and with your authorization, the APP may collect your blood pressure, blood sugar, heart rate and other data for syncing to the App - your personal health data.
Usage information:
We may collect information about how you use the App, including your device type, operating system, IP address, and other technical details.
How do we use your information?
We may use the information we collect for the following purposes:
To provide the App's features and services to you;
To improve the App and develop new features and services;
To communicate with you about the App and your use of it;
To personalize your experience with the App;
To comply with legal and regulatory requirements;
To carry out marketing campaigns: The app includes targeted push.
How do we share your information?
We may share your information with third-party service providers who help us operate the App and provide the services you request. We may also share your information with our affiliates and business partners or in response to a legal request or court order.
How do we protect your information?
We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, and disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
Your rights and choices
You have the right to access and correct your personal information. You may also choose to delete your account and personal data anytime.
Changes to this policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes to this policy, we will notify you by email or by posting a notice on the App.
Attention
The data and conclusions provided in this application are for informational purposes only and are not a substitute for professional medical advice or diagnosis. They do not replace professional medical equipment or the judgment of a medical professional. Always consult a qualified medical professional if you have any health concerns.
